headline: Wyoming State Buys European Bank Stocks, Adjusts Healthcare Holdings
summary: The state of Wyoming initiated a position in two European banks during the second quarter and made changes to its holdings in the broad healthcare sector.  A Form 13-F filed with the U.S. Securities and Exchange Commission on Aug. 19 shows the 44th state initiated a position in  Barclays  and  Banco Santander  during the second quarter.  Wyoming owned 6,371 Barclays shares and 15,638 Banco Santander shares as of June 30.
